## Hints for Future Agents

- When rebasing a long-lived branch onto a new base, first check the
  reflog state (`git reflog`) and confirm whether the original commits
  carry meaningful history. If they're all "test"/"wip" checkpoints,
  reset-and-recommit is faster than fighting line-by-line conflicts.
- `git checkout <old-ref> -- <file>` is great for files that are
  pure-adds. For files that exist on both branches and have diverged
  (here: `patch.py`, `pyproject.toml`), do surgical edits on the
  new-base version instead — checking them out wholesale would revert
  unrelated master changes.
- The `patch_mcp` → `patch_fastmcp` rename across master between the
  ADK branch's original base and origin/master was the specific reason
  `patch.py` could not be checked out wholesale.
- After force-push, PR #6841 will show the cleaner diff (just ADK +
  semconv) and the semconv portion will disappear on top once #6916
  merges, leaving only ADK.

## Codebase Discoveries

